snippet: Witnesses said that protests did not resume over the devaluation of the currency, the rial, and black-market money traders and prospective customers stayed away.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Thomas Erdbrink from Tehran, Sangar Rahimi from Kabul, Afghanistan, and James Kanter from Paris.

lead_paragraph: Witnesses said that protests did not resume over the devaluation of the currency, the rial, and black-market money traders and prospective customers stayed away.

headline.seo: Tehran Merchants Reopen, With Police Watching
headline.main: Merchants Reopen in Tehran, With Police Watching for More Protests
headline.print_headline: Merchants Reopen in Tehran, With Police Watching for More Protests
